##### **Create Your Better Tomorrow**


With over 50 years of experience in the industry, Kollmorgen, a Regal Rexnord brand, is a technology leader in navigation and fleet control of automated guided vehicles (AGVs) and autonomous mobile robots (AMRs). In our continued effort to innovate and grow, we are now expanding and are seeking talents to join us and be part of our success story.


Our definition of success goes beyond customer satisfaction; it includes fostering the talent of tomorrow. At Kollmorgen, we cultivate a collaborative and inclusive environment where innovation thrives and every individual is valued. Our commitment to professional growth and development ensures that you will have the opportunity to advance your career while working on cutting-edge automation solutions.





##### **We are looking for a DevOps Engineer to be part of a dynamic team that is passionate about making a difference in the world of AGVs and AMRs.**

##### **Position Overview**


As a DevOps Engineer, you will be part of our Engineering department, along with other 70+ engineers working within embedded systems, system software as well as Windows applications and web services.


You will be a key player in our System team, a specialized Agile team that assists in building and supporting Agile development environments, including developing and maintaining the continuous delivery pipeline. You will also support the integration of software modules, end-to-end solution testing, DevOps practices, deployment, and release.


The mission of this position is to bridge the gap between development and IT operations, ensuring smooth, efficient, and automated software delivery processes.

##### **What does success look like in this position:**

* **Efficient CI/CD Pipeline Management**: Successfully implement and manage CI/CD pipelines, automating infrastructure management and repetitive tasks to ensure smooth software delivery;
* **Reliable Infrastructure:** Maintain a secure and reliable development infrastructure and tools, ensuring high availability and performance;
* **Effective Risk Mitigation:** Proactively identify and mitigate high-level risks, enhancing security practices across all systems;
* **Seamless Collaboration:** Foster effective collaboration with development teams to integrate new features and improvements smoothly;
* **Leadership in Projects:** Lead infrastructure projects effectively, manage cloud services, and standardize tool usage across the CI/CD pipeline for consistency and efficiency;
* **Proactive System Monitoring:** Implement robust monitoring and logging systems, continuously proposing and implementing standards and improvements for the development environment;
* **Stakeholder Engagement:** Actively engage with stakeholders outside of the development teams in the release train, addressing and resolving environment issues promptly;
* **Unified Product Handling****:** Ensure unified handling of third-party products and licenses, meeting business needs and maintaining service reliability.

##### **To achieve the mission and success of this position, we believe you already have:**

* University degree in engineering;
* 3 years of working experience in a DevOps role or similar position;
* Experience with configuration management and version control systems such as GitLab and SVN;
* Strong knowledge of cloud platforms such as AWS, Azure, etc.;
* Proficiency in scripting languages such as Python or Bash;
* Familiarity with containerization technologies such as Docker and Kubernetes;
* Experience with virtualization technologies such as Microsoft Hyper-V and VMware vSphere;
* Work experience in implementing and managing CI/CD pipelines;
* Ability to anticipate, address, and solve problems proactively;
* Strong communication and collaboration skills;
* Commitment to continuous learning and adaptability;
* Proficiency in English, both written and verbal.

##### **We find it beneficial if you have:**

* Knowledge of AMR & AGV domain;
* AWS Certified DevOps Engineer or similar certification;
* Software development experience.


We see that our ideal candidates are committed to personal & professional growth, and they share our core values and genuine enthusiasm for innovation.




##### **Additional Information**


Full time employment | Based in Mölndal, Sweden


Selection takes place on an ongoing basis, so be sure to apply early. We're excited to hear from you!

##### **Kollmorgen - Autonomous Mobile Solutions**


We offer a complete automation solution for AGV and AMR providers. Our NDC Solutions platform is a proven platform that enables efficient and reliable vehicle automation with increased performance. It includes all hardware, software, and navigation technologies necessary to automate a vehicle fleet. The platform has been installed in a vast variety of material handling sites and vehicles across the globe.

Your Job Title: Manufacturing Engineer
Job Location: Sweden - Danderyd (on-site)
Job Summary
As a Manufacturing Engineer, you will play a crucial role in supporting our production lines and technicians. You will be responsible for ESD management, component fault analysis and repair, and overseeing the test run process. Your expertise will be vital in maintaining high standards of quality and efficiency in our electronics manufacturing processes.
Production Support overall tasks:* Be a technical support function for production, Development, SQA and purchasing;
* Responsible for detailed technical troubleshooting in production equipment and products;
* Act as a link between Development, Manufacturing Development or other departments towards production;
* Escalate product and process problems that can prevent deliveries.


Job responsibilities:* Provide technical support to production to ensure delivery reliability;
* Analyze and address deviations in products and equipment;
* Monitor and improve ergonomics in production;
* Drive process improvements and implement enhanced working methods;
* Follow established processes, work instructions, and assembly instructions;
* Collaborate with group leaders to identify and plan preventive activities;
* Statistically monitor, measure, and analyze process quality;
* Maintain and calibrate production equipment, updating System-Q as needed;
* Maintain and update calibration and work instructions;
* Introduce change order processes and test series in production;
* Ensure quality information is disseminated to relevant managers;
* Participate in production reviews during the development process;
* Train production personnel on equipment and methods;
* Analyze and resolve Defect Product Returns (DPRs);
* Support other departments with tests and investigations;
* Lead projects related to production equipment development.


Authorities:* Take necessary measures within your area of expertise in consultation with relevant managers.


Competence Requirements:* Bachelor's Degree within Electronics or Mechatronics field;
* Strong expertise in Electronics, Mechanics, Optics, Production Technology, Project Management or Quality Work;
* Excellent knowledge of both Swedish and English;
* Proficiency in MS Office and Google programs;
* Strong communication skills.


Why Join Us? At Trimble Inc. we value innovation, collaboration, and continuous improvement. You will have the opportunity to work on exciting projects, lead initiatives, and contribute to the success of our production processes. We offer a supportive work environment, professional development opportunities, and a chance to make a real impact.
Join us and be a part of our journey towards excellence in manufacturing!
About Trimble:  

Dedicated to the world’s tomorrow, Trimble is a technology company delivering solutions that enable our customers to work in new ways to measure, build, grow and move goods for a better quality of life. Core technologies in positioning, modelling, connectivity and data analytics connect the digital and physical worlds to improve productivity, quality, safety, transparency and sustainability. From purpose-built products and enterprise lifecycle solutions to industry cloud services, Trimble is transforming critical industries such as construction, geospatial, agriculture and transportation to power an interconnected world of work. For more information about Trimble (NASDAQ: TRMB), visit: www.trimble.com  

Trimble’s Inclusiveness Commitment:  

We believe in celebrating our differences. That is why our diversity is our strength. To us, that means actively participating in opportunities to be inclusive. Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion have guided our current success while also moving our desire to improve. We actively seek to add members to our community who represent our customers and the places we live and work.  

